# the stylistic construction of the syntactic structures a
~~dissertation submitted to the council of the college of arts -
~~universuty of baghdad in partila fulfilment of the requirements of the
~~degree of doctor of philosophy in arabic. by mahdi hamed mustafa al-
~~said 'ali al-'ani supervised by assistant professor dr. huda muhammad
~~s. al- hadithi 1424 a. h. ... 2003 a. d. PageV00P0000
# abstract this study aims at investigating the stylistic construction
~~of the syntactic structures in arabic according to the modern linguistic
~~points of view. it deals with syntax and semantics as two important
~~aspects of studying arabic where none of the grammarians denies that the
~~construction of the syntactic structures consists of two parts ; the
~~subject and the object that are expressed by sibewaih as none occurs
~~without being accompanied by the other. he elaborates on the levels
~~speech construction ; al - mustaqim , al - hasin , al - kabeeeh and al -
~~muhad , by which he establishes the first theory that later on governs
~~the research in syntax. this study tries to denote to the diversity of
~~the syntactic structure and that of the vocabulary item from which it is
~~composed. for instance , the syntactic structure may consist of two
~~nouns , a verb and a noun , two structures , a verb and a noun plus a
~~prepositional phrase or an adverb , a verb and three nouns ... etc. , by
~~which the type and the form of that syntactic structure is determined.
~~while studying these structures , the researcher identifies certain
~~terms such as the simplified , the extended , the interrelated , the
~~double , and the interwoven structures. this study proves that the
~~number of the elements from which the syntactic structure is constructed
~~do not exceed more than three elements. these are the noun , the verb ,
~~and the letter in spite of diversity of its types and forms. this leads
~~the researcher to investigate the contruction of the syntactic structure
~~and its types real and symbolic refrences and to apply them to a large
~~number of literary texts and syntactic evidence as governed by the texts
~~of the qura'an. the researcher accordingly explains that stylistics
~~deals with the construction of PageV12P0001
# the syntactic structure as an important element when studying the
~~characteristics that from the text. the researcher states that the
~~aspects of modernism cannot be expressed in the syntactic and semantic
~~studies away from the realization of the elements of the heritage and
~~the investigation of their originality although our estimation of that
~~heritage does not prevent as from making objective assessment on the
~~basis of modern speculation. the emergence of the level upon which we
~~depend to construct the syntactic structure should not be limited
~~neither to the agreement of construction of that structure with the
~~linguistic rules nor to the absence of this agreement because each
~~structure has its own characteristics that present its creative feature
~~either with its agreement or disagreement with the linguistic rule and
~~according to what surrounds it such as the situation , the setting and
~~the intended purpose. the researcher divides his dissertation into three
~~chapters preceded by introduction and ended with conclusions. the
~~introduction presents the relationship between syntax and semantics in
~~order to introduce the scope of this topic and its details. the first
~~chapter is devoted to the study of the syntactic relations and its
~~basics. it falls into three sections. the first studies the concept ,
~~types and forms of the syntactic structure. the second explains the
~~methods of understanding the meaning of the structure. the third shows
~~how meaning is expressed by the structure. the second chapter introduces
~~the levels of constructing the syntactic structure. it also falls into
~~three sections. the first is about the construction of the declarative ,
~~statement and the request structures. the second shows the additive
~~meaning techniques. the third studies the level of construction
~~regarding the apparent meaning of the text and its interpretation.
~~PageV12P0002
# the third chapter studies within three sections the conformity of the
~~structure to the situation. the first deals with the arrangement of the
~~parts of the structure. the second identifies the use and the neglegance
~~of using the verbs and articles. the third is concerned with the style ,
~~context and setting. the study ends with the conclusions that the
~~researcher arrives at through his research and the obtained results
~~followed by bibliography of the sources reviewed both in arabic and
~~english. mr. mahdi hamed. m. al-'ani arabic dept. , college of arts,
~~universuty of baghdad november 2003 a. d PageV12P0003

